<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf00e530e-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7471"><num value="7471">§ 7471.</num><heading> Suspension or termination</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idf00e530f-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7471/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If the Secretary finds that an order issued under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s7463">section 7463 of this title</ref>, or a provision of the order, obstructs or does not tend to effectuate the purposes of this subchapter, the Secretary shall suspend or terminate the operation of the order or provision.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idf00e5310-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7471/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Limitation</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The suspension or termination of any order, or any provision of an order, shall not be considered an order under this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf00e5311-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/104/127/tV/s562">Pub. L. 104–127, title V, § 562</ref>, <date date="1996-04-04">Apr. 4, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/1074">110 Stat. 1074</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
